# Documentation Structure

`AGENTS.md` is a **map** (~80 lines). Details live in `docs/`.

```
AGENTS.md              ← entry point for agents; pointers only
docs/
├── architecture.md    ← layers, naming, how to add a module
├── coding-rules.md    ← coding standards and pitfalls
├── testing.md         ← full testing guide
├── migrations.md      ← Alembic workflow
├── DESIGN.md          ← subsystem design (auth, reputation, match lifecycle)
├── SECURITY.md        ← security model
├── RELIABILITY.md     ← reliability patterns
├── QUALITY_SCORE.md   ← quality gates and CI standards
├── PLANS.md           ← roadmap and phase tracking
├── PRODUCT_SENSE.md   ← product vision and principles
├── PRD.md             ← full product requirements
├── design-docs/       ← engineering design decisions (ADR-style)
├── exec-plans/        ← active and completed execution plans
├── generated/         ← auto-generated docs (db-schema, etc.)
├── product-specs/     ← per-feature product specs
└── references/        ← llms.txt library references
```

## Rules

- Never put detailed rules or long content directly in `AGENTS.md`.
- When adding new documentation, create a focused file in `docs/` and add a pointer in `AGENTS.md`.
- `exec-plans/active/` = in-flight work; `exec-plans/completed/` = done.
- `docs/generated/` contains auto-generated files — do not hand-edit them.
